00:21:58.000 --> 00:21:59.420
middle of the screen.

00:21:59.420 --> 00:22:02.280
So I like this just because
it really simplifies

00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:04.090
the look and feel.

00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:08.520
It brings the content out, and
it sticks to the roots of what

00:22:08.520 --> 00:22:11.880
the app is trying to do here--
measure the speed and show

00:22:11.880 --> 00:22:14.490
your historical entries.

00:22:14.490 --> 00:22:16.325
NICK BUTCHER: It also has
elements of the new clock app

00:22:16.325 --> 00:22:19.500
I think, that new stopwatch app
that shipped with Android

00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:21.630
4.2, which I think
is a good thing.

00:22:21.630 --> 00:22:23.070
ADAM KOCH: Yeah, I agree.

00:22:23.070 --> 00:22:25.780
So not much else to comment
here other than I think it

00:22:25.780 --> 00:22:26.540
looks really nice.

00:22:26.540 --> 00:22:28.400
The Holo thing is great.

00:22:28.400 --> 00:22:31.580
And it really sticks to a sort
of main navigation we would

00:22:31.580 --> 00:22:33.560
recommend for an
app like this--

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:37.620
Menu button, action bar, tabs
and then two content panes on

00:22:37.620 --> 00:22:38.700
the tablet UI.

00:22:38.700 --> 00:22:40.380
ROMAN NURIK: I think the other
thing I just want to point out

00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:43.800
for the tablet UI is look how
much you can do just changing

00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.850
metrics, just changing
dimensions.

00:22:45.850 --> 00:22:46.880
The only difference--

00:22:46.880 --> 00:22:49.180
and I'm guessing that the assets
are probably the same.

00:22:49.180 --> 00:22:50.530
They're probably not even
using the assets.

00:22:50.530 --> 00:22:52.820
This is probably some custom
drawing if you were to

00:22:52.820 --> 00:22:54.220
implement this.

00:22:54.220 --> 00:22:56.660
But the font sizes are
slightly larger.

00:22:56.660 --> 00:22:59.150
The spacing between elements
is slightly larger.

00:22:59.150 --> 00:23:01.370
The size of that circle
is obviously larger.

00:23:01.370 --> 00:23:05.440
But then it's really just about
spacing, font size, and

00:23:05.440 --> 00:23:08.052
just dimensions and metrics, and
then obviously, if you're

00:23:08.052 --> 00:23:11.380
showing images, showing those
images at full resolution.

00:23:11.380 --> 00:23:14.870
But it really shows the power
of what you can do with just

00:23:14.870 --> 00:23:15.680
dimensions.

00:23:15.680 --> 00:23:18.370
So for developers out there,
if you just extract your

00:23:18.370 --> 00:23:21.220
dimensions into dimension
resources, you don't even have

00:23:21.220 --> 00:23:23.430
to create a tablet-specific
layout in a lot of cases.

00:23:23.430 --> 00:23:25.150
You just change the dimensions
for tablets.

00:23:25.150 --> 00:23:26.690
ADAM KOCH: Yep.

00:23:26.690 --> 00:23:28.985
Good job, Glenn Barker.

00:23:28.985 --> 00:23:30.490
NICK BUTCHER: Yeah, I guess
the takeaway from the

00:23:30.490 --> 00:23:33.150
designers for that is don't be
scared about having something

00:23:33.150 --> 00:23:35.790
that looks similar, but then
you call out different

00:23:35.790 --> 00:23:38.000
switching points at which you
say the text size should be

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:40.260
larger because that's really
easy for developers to do.

00:23:40.260 --> 00:23:41.970
ROMAN NURIK: Yeah, exactly.

00:23:41.970 --> 00:23:44.540
We should probably do a future
episode on how to best

00:23:44.540 --> 00:23:46.780
